body_html:
@soumith I encountered error in nightly build 2018.04.09 and narrowed down the cause to different import order:

import torch
import tensorboardX
# fine
import tensorboardX
import torch
# error, see https://gist.github.com/lanpa/af92011358181a45e959b3b35ea0533d

But if I build master from source, both of them works fine.

update: replacing import tensorboardX with import cv2 results in same behavior.

body:
@soumith I encountered error in nightly build 2018.04.09 and narrowed down the cause to different import order:
``` python
import torch
import tensorboardX
# fine
```
``` python
import tensorboardX
import torch
# error, see https://gist.github.com/lanpa/af92011358181a45e959b3b35ea0533d
```
But if I build master from source, both of them works fine.


update: replacing import tensorboardX with import cv2 results in same behavior.
